itemDescription: British naval officer and psychic researcher

wikipedia_page.main: Vice admiral William Usborne Moore (March 8, 1849 – March 15, 1918) also known as W. Usborne Moore was a British naval commander, psychical researcher and spiritualist.

response: Macclesfield banks were named after the British naval ship, HMS Macclesfield, which ran aground in the vicinity of these shoals in 1804. In April 1888 the banks were surveyed by , under the command of William Usborne Moore, with Percy Bassett-Smith as Surgeon-Naturalist. They found a depth of  inside the bank, with the rim rising to within  of the surface. Dredging found live corals, showing that although entirely submerged, the bank was an actively growing reef.
